org.onehippo.forge.channelmanager.pagesupport.channel.event

Class DocumentCopyingPageCopyEventListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.onehippo.forge.channelmanager.pagesupport.channel.event.DocumentCopyingPageCopyEventListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.hippoecm.hst.core.container.ComponentManagerAware

    public class DocumentCopyingPageCopyEventListener
extends Object
implements org.hippoecm.hst.core.container.ComponentManagerAware
    org.hippoecm.hst.pagecomposer.jaxrs.api.PageCopyEvent event handler which is to be registered through ComponentManager.registerEventSubscriber(Object) and unregistered through ComponentManager.unregisterEventSubscriber(Object) during the HST-2 based web application lifecycle.

    Basically this event handler scans all the linked documents in a page and its components and copy each document from the source channel to the target channel if not existing in the target channel.
